le":"1220–Deceased","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–Deceased","about 1250":"about 1250","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Calveley","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Calveley (Cheshire)."],"variants":[{"name":"Calverley","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): habitational name from Calverley in Yorkshire, named with Old English <i>calfra</i> (genitive plural of <i>calf</i> ‘calf’) + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’. Alternatively, in some instances the name may be a variant of the habitational name <b>Calveley</b>, from a place so called in Cheshire (with the same meaning as above), or from Calverleigh in Devon, meaning ‘the clearing of the bare wood’ (Old English <i>calu</i> ‘bare, bald’ + <i>wudu</i> ‘wood’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’)."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Calveley was born in 1225. She had at least 1 son with Richard de Delves."},"et":{"1225–":"1225–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"England"},"fi":{"1225–":"1225–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"England"},"fr":{"1225–":"1225–Décédée","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","about 1250":"environ 1250","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Margaret Calveley est née en 1225. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Richard de Delves."},"de":{"1225–":"1225–Verstorben","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–Verstorben","about 1250":"um 1250","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Margaret Calveley wurde 1225 geboren. Sie hatte mit Richard de Delves mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1225–":"1225–Desede","1220–Male":"1220–Desede","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–Desede","about 1250":"about 1250","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"England"},"hu":{"1225–":"1225–elhunyt","1220–Male":"1220–elhunyt","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":"1225–elhunyt","about 1250":"1250 körül","1225":"1225","1220":"1220","1250":"1250","1281":"1281","England":"England"},"id":{"1225–":"1225–Telah Meninggal","1220–Male":"1220–Telah Meninggal","1250–1281":"1250–1281","1225–Female":